com.djrapitops.plugin.command

Class CommandNode

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.djrapitops.plugin.command.CommandNode
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    HelpCommand, TreeCmdNode

    public abstract class CommandNode
extends Object
    Represents a command, or sub-command.

    Various setters should be called in the constructor to allow full use of HelpCommand.

    Author:
    Rsl1122

    • Constructor Detail

      • CommandNode

        public CommandNode(String aliases,
                   String permission,
                   CommandType commandType)
        Create a new CommandNode.

        It is recommended to call following methods during construction: setShortHelp(String) setInDepthHelp(String...) setArguments(String...)

        Parameters:
        aliases - Aliases of this command, separated with a '|' - eg. one|two|three, First alias will be regarded as the name of this command.
        permission - Permission required to use this node.
        commandType - CommandType sender requirements for this command.

      • onCommand

        public abstract void onCommand(Sender sender,
                               String commandLabel,
                               String[] args)
        Implement this method for the command do do something.
        Parameters:
        sender - entity that sent the command.
        commandLabel - Label defined by Bukkit or an empty string.
        args - Arguments given to the command, not including the command name.

      • getInDepthHelp

        public String[] getInDepthHelp()
        Retrieve in depth instructions on what the command is used for.

        If in depth help is not defined, short help will be displayed instead.

        Returns:
        For example: "This is used for finding players", "Use with caution"

      • setInDepthHelp

        protected CommandNode setInDepthHelp(String... inDepthHelp)
        Set in depth instructions on what the command is used for. Each String is it's own row when in depth help is displayed.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
        The current node, for builder like calls.
